params._cycleTarget: Funding target for the dominant assurance cycle/campaign.
params._duration: The duration of the cycle in seconds.
params._ipfsCID: The CID obtained from IPFS for uploading project's metadata. Hardcoded here for Hackathon purposes
params._maxEarlyPledgers: Maximum allowed early plegers for funding cycle.
params._minimumPledgeAmount: Minimum amount that payers can pledge.
params._owner: The address to set as the owner of the project. The project's ERC-721 will be owned by this address.
params._startTime: The timestamp that the cycle is desired to start.

returns._projectID: The ID of the newly configured project.

reconfigureFundingCyclesOf(uint256,uint8.details: Only a project's owner or operator can configure its funding cycles. We need to again use the same delegate/DominantJuice contract address. Based on cycle results, the next cycle needs to be reconfigured accordingly before the cycle is over. See the result parameter below.

params._projectId: The ID of the project for which funding cycles are being reconfigured.
params.result: Campaign result: 0 = too close to call; set frozen cycle, 1 = success, 2 = failure,

returns.configuration: The configuration of the successfully reconfigured funding cycle.

delegateDeployer().notice: The contract responsible for deploying the delegate.

launchProjectFor(address,string,uint256,.notice: Launches a new project with a delegate attached.

reconfigureFundingCyclesOf(uint256,uint8.notice: Reconfigures funding cycles for a project with an attached delegate.
